The paper discusses the implementation of a neural network model for question answering, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of Bi-directional attention flow layer and LSTM encoder suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the use of smart-span equation and the focus on improving prediction accuracy suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
